he first national fitness drive was ultimately a failure. Drawing on extensive research, Strong, Beautiful and Modern is a lively investigation into the way people and their governments think about health and well-being, and how historical views have shaped our modern life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPhysical fitnessxGovernment policyzAustraliaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPhysical fitnessxGovernment policyzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPhysical fitnessxGovernment policyzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aPhysical fitnessxGovernment policyzNew ZealandxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Australia & New Zealand.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482530640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774825306423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774825306/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles